---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/docs.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Data Security — Airlock">
    <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Data Security</h1>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-1">
                How Airlock protects your data at every layer
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
            <!-- Architecture Overview -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Security Architecture
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Airlock is built on the <a
                        href="https://harp-protocol.github.io/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        class="text-link hover:underline"
                        >HARP protocol</a
                    > (Human Approval Relay Protocol), designed so that no single
                    component — including the Airlock Gateway itself — can access
                    sensitive data. Security is enforced through cryptography, not
                    trust.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- End-to-End Encryption -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    End-to-End Encryption
                </h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-4">
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-border/50 bg-card/50"
                    >
                        <h3 class="font-medium text-sm mb-2">
                            Payload Encryption
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
                            All AI action payloads (commands, file diffs,
                            terminal output) are encrypted with <strong
                                >AES-256-GCM</strong
                            > using a symmetric key shared only between the enforcer
                            and the approver. The Gateway processes only opaque ciphertext.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-border/50 bg-card/50"
                    >
                        <h3 class="font-medium text-sm mb-2">Key Management</h3>
                        <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
                            Encryption keys are generated during workspace
                            pairing and stored locally on the enforcer and the
                            approver device. Keys are <strong
                                >never transmitted to or stored on the Gateway</strong
                            >.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Cryptographic Signatures -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Cryptographic Signatures
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Approval decisions are cryptographically signed using <strong
                        >Ed25519</strong
                    > digital signatures. The approver's private key never leaves
                    their mobile device. The enforcer verifies the signature locally
                    before allowing any AI action to execute.
                </p>
                <div
                    class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-border/50 bg-muted/30 mt-4"
                >
                    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                        <strong class="text-foreground"
                            >Signature verification is local.</strong
                        > Even if the Gateway were compromised, forged approvals would
                        fail signature verification at the enforcer. This is the core
                        security guarantee of the HARP protocol.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Zero-Knowledge Relay -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Zero-Knowledge Gateway
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    The Airlock Gateway operates as a zero-knowledge relay with
                    strict guarantees:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >No payload access:</strong
                        > The Gateway relays encrypted artifacts without decryption
                        capability
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >No key material:</strong
                        > Encryption keys and signing keys are never transmitted to
                        the Gateway
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Log redaction:</strong
                        > A dedicated <code
                            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                            >RedactionMiddleware</code
                        > strips sensitive headers and prevents payload data from
                        appearing in logs, traces, or error reports
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Minimal push notifications:</strong
                        > Push notifications contain only request IDs and artifact
                        type labels — no payload content
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- Fail-Closed Enforcement -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Fail-Closed Enforcement
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    All Airlock enforcer extensions operate in <strong
                        >fail-closed</strong
                    > mode. If any part of the approval flow fails, the AI action
                    is blocked:
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mt-4">
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            Gateway unreachable → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            Invalid signature → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            Request timeout → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            JSON parse error → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            Missing routing token → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-3 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5"
                    >
                        <p class="text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                            Submission error → Blocked
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Transport Security -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Transport Security
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    In addition to end-to-end encryption, the Gateway enforces:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>HTTPS/TLS
                        for all API communication
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><code
                            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                            >X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff</code
                        > to prevent MIME-type sniffing
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><code
                            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                            >X-Frame-Options: DENY</code
                        > to prevent clickjacking
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><code
                            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                            >Cache-Control: no-store</code
                        > to prevent caching of sensitive responses
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><code
                            class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                            >Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin</code>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- Canonical Hashing -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Integrity Verification
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Every artifact is canonicalized using <strong
                        >JSON Canonicalization Scheme (JCS / RFC 8785)</strong
                    > before hashing with SHA-256. This produces a deterministic <code
                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                        >artifactHash</code
                    > that both the enforcer and approver can independently verify,
                    ensuring no tampering occurred in transit.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Open Source Components -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Open Source & Auditability
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    The following components are open source for independent
                    audit:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >HARP Protocol Specification:</strong
                        > Full protocol spec with test vectors and compliance criteria
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Enforcer Extensions:</strong
                        > Cursor, Windsurf, Antigravity, and Copilot enforcers
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Gateway API Client:</strong
                        > The client library for gateway integration (coming soon)
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- Summary Table -->
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    Security Summary
                </h2>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table class="w-full text-sm mt-4">
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
                                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 font-semibold"
                                    >Layer</th
                                >
                                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 font-semibold"
                                    >Mechanism</th
                                >
                                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold"
                                    >Standard</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="text-muted-foreground">
                            <tr class="border-b border-border/30">
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Payload Encryption</td>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Symmetric AEAD</td>
                                <td class="py-3"
                                    ><code
                                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                                        >AES-256-GCM</code
                                    ></td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="border-b border-border/30">
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Decision Signing</td>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Digital Signatures</td>
                                <td class="py-3"
                                    ><code
                                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                                        >Ed25519</code
                                    ></td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="border-b border-border/30">
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Artifact Integrity</td>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Canonical Hashing</td>
                                <td class="py-3"
                                    ><code
                                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                                        >JCS + SHA-256</code
                                    ></td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="border-b border-border/30">
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Transport</td>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Channel Encryption</td>
                                <td class="py-3"
                                    ><code
                                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                                        >TLS 1.2+</code
                                    ></td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Failure Mode</td>
                                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Fail-Closed</td>
                                <td class="py-3"
                                    ><code
                                        class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-muted text-xs font-mono"
                                        >Block on any error</code
                                    ></td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 flex gap-4">
            <a href="/docs" class="text-sm text-link hover:underline"
                >← All Docs</a
            >
            <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:underline"
                >Back to Airlock</a
            >
        </div>
    </div>
</DocsLayout>
